Description: Papyrus fragment bearing remains of 4 lines of a Coptic text written against the fibres (verso), the other 2 lines written along the fibres (recto).
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380772) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380772)
Ede 1972- / Writing and lettering in antiquity (no. 58)
